output.map_title: Map to show the number of graduates of Medicine and dentistry now working in Education who are currently living in each region five years after graduation, male and female first degree graduates from English HEIs, APs and FECs, 2019/20 tax year.
output.maptext: For first degree graduates of Medicine and dentistry in the Education industry five years after graduation, the region where the most graduates had studied was London. The region where the fewest graduates had studied was East Midlands. The region where the highest number of graduates lived five years after graduation was London and the regions where the fewest graduates lived were East Midlands, North West, South East, West Midlands and Yorkshire and the Humber.
output.maptext2: For first degree graduates of Medicine and dentistry in the Education industry, the regions with the most graduates living there five years after graduation, compared to the number having studied in the region were East of England, North East and South West, where the number of graduates was the same as the number of students.The regions with the largest decrease were North West, South East, West Midlands and Yorkshire and the Humber where the number of graduates decreased by -100%.
